<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="499" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d499">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1173</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Gonzales</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 302</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 9, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 422
                            of the 28th ultimo in which you enclose a translation of a letter
                            addressed to you by General José Miguel Gómez, styled President of the
                            Liberal Directory and General Commanding the Constitutional Army.</p>
                        <pb facs="0548" n="382" xml:id="pg_382"/>
                        <p>It appears to the Department that you need not reply to General Gómez’s
                            letter.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank L. Polk</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>